Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author task-setup
    Description Container for timezone/locale audit task

%post
    set -e

    # Ensure basic tools are present
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        locales \
        tzdata \
        ca-certificates

    # Install pytest for the grading test suite
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Guarantee /etc/timezone exists with the expected content
    echo "Etc/UTC" > /etc/timezone

    # Create a writable working directory for the student
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Clean up apt caches to keep the image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Provide the expected LANG value for the grading tests
    export LANG=C.UTF-8
    export LC_ALL=C.UTF-8

%runscript
    exec /bin/bash "$@"

%help
    This container provides the baseline environment for the timezone/locale
    compliance audit task.  The student must create /home/user/audit/
    and the required log file as specified in the assignment.  Pytest is
    pre-installed so that the automated grading suite can run.